Alachua County Library District Tools Locations Contact Get a Card My Account Catalog Events FAQs Website Support Volunteer You can support the Alachua County Library District in many ways, including volunteering at a library or with Friends of the Library and the Alachua County Library District Foundation . Give a Gift Your personal gift or organization’s gift to the library in memory of a friend or loved one provides a lasting tribute which benefits the entire community. Celebrate happy times such as the birthday of a child or special friend with a gift to the library in their name. Each book will contain a gift plate with your name as donor and the name of the person honored. You may earmark the funds for materials in your particular area of interest. You may also mail your check with a gift form , available at all service desks, to: Alachua County Library District: Donations 401 E. University Ave. Gainesville, FL 32601 Friends of the Library Image Friends of the Library is an all-volunteer nonprofit in Gainesville run independently of the Alachua County Library District. The organization supports the Library District and literacy programs throughout Alachua County. Friends of the Library is well-known for popular bi-annual book sales held at the Bookhouse located at 430-B N Main St, Gainesville, FL 32601. The organization accepts donations of books, records, art, and more for the sale. Please contact FOL for donation times, sale details, and membership information. 352-375-1676 folacld.org Alachua County Library District Foundation Image The Alachua County Library District Foundation is a nonprofit organization with the mission of providing supplemental funding to the library with an emphasis on long-term support and planned giving. To learn more, visit www.acldfound.com . Alachua County Library District Tools Locations Contact Get a Card My Account Catalog Events FAQs Website About Alachua County Library District is an independent special district and the sole provider of public library services to approximately 271,000 citizens in Alachua County, serving urban and rural communities through 12 branch locations, two bookmobiles, and multiple deposit collections. Its goal is to provide all community members with free, open and equal access to education, information, and entertainment.The Library District’s mission is to build a better community by creating opportunities to participate, connect, and discover.
